<p>I have one field named 'uniqueCode' which formed using city and salesPersonId and some count. <strong>format:</strong> uniqueCode = City + SalesPersonId + 101 <strong>example:</strong>    AHM1101=AHM+1+101 Now, I want a method which would take city and salespersonId and return me max of uniqueId. I have written query like this:</p>  <pre><code>@Query("SELECT max(s.uniqueCode) FROM ServiceProvider s WHERE s.uniqueCode LIKE :cityCode:salesPersonId%") public String maxUniqueCode(@Param("cityCode") String cityCode, @Param("salesPersonId") Long salesPersonId); </code></pre>  <p>But it is giving error that <strong>Unexpected token: salesPersonId</strong> . What is the correct way to write this query. Thanks.</p>